### Create user 1
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user1",
  "email": "user1@example.com"
}

###

### List all users
GET http://localhost:8080/users

###

### Create user 2
POST http://localhost:8080/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user2",
  "email": "user2@example.com"
}

###

### List all users (should show two)
GET http://localhost:8080/users

###

### User 1 creates poll
POST http://localhost:8080/polls
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Best OS?",
  "publishedAt": "2025-10-21T12:00:00Z",
  "validUntil": "2025-10-28T12:00:00Z",
  "creatorId": 1,
  "options": [
    { "caption": "Linux", "presentationOrder": 1 },
    { "caption": "Windows", "presentationOrder": 2 }
  ]
}

###

### List polls (see created poll)
GET http://localhost:8080/polls

###

### User 2 votes on first option (Linux) with +1
POST http://localhost:8080/votes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 2,
  "optionId": 1,
  "value": 1
}

###

### User 2 changes vote to -1
POST http://localhost:8080/votes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": 2,
  "optionId": 1,
  "value": -1
}

###

### List all votes
GET http://localhost:8080/votes

###

### Delete the poll
DELETE http://localhost:8080/polls/1

###

### List votes again (should be empty now)
GET http://localhost:8080/votes
